  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Research hypothesis:

      Does delayed primary wound closure after appendectomy in adults with complicated appendicitis
      reduce postoperative superficial surgical site infection compare to primary wound closure.

      Study design:

      This study is a multicenter randomized controlled trial of delay versus primary wound closure
      in complicated appendicitis.

      Setting:

      Thammasat Hospital, Ramathibodi Hospital, Chonburi Hospital, Chonpratarn Hospital, Vachira
      Hospital, and Pathumthani Hospital

      Participants:

      Adult patients age 18 years or older and non-pregnant in women who have been diagnosed as
      gangrenous or ruptured appendicitis.

      Outcome:

      Superficial surgical site infection

      Period of study:

      August 2012 - August 2014
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
